        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP" source="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EPANRKPM">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>ἐτελεύτησ
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>εν <persName type="attested"><name>Ἀγάθη</name></persName> χρη
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>στιανὴ μηνὶ
                    <lb n="4"/>μαίῳ ἀπὸ <expan><abbr>κ</abbr><ex>α</ex><abbr><hi rend="small">λ</hi></abbr><ex>ανδῶν</ex></expan> <num value="14">ιδ</num>
                    <lb n="5"/>λοιπὸν <num value="17">ιζ</num>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text of Agnello 1953</note></app>
                    <app loc="3"><note>Rizzone: στιαν (η omitted by error?)</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Agathe, a Christian, died in the month of May, 14 (days) from the kalends, 17 (days) remaining (to the end of the month)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The dating formula is unusual, but is attested in the Rabat catacomb in Malta (so Rizzone).</p>
            </div>
